description:
&lt;p&gt;Business Support Administrator&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Band 4&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;37.5 hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an enthusiastic and motivated individual to join our Community Administration Team. We are currently involved in developing a Single Point of Access Service and the majority of the teams you support will sit within this service so experience of working in an environment with high volume of telephone calls is desirable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be responsible for the management and leadership of the administration team based in various sites throughout the Stockport area. Leading and supporting staff within your team is a key responsibility and you will have previous experience of managing a team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting role for those with significant leadership and administration experience. No two days are the same and you will face challenges and demands which you will be able to meet with the help and support of your team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to meet deadlines and promote efficiencies is a key part of this role so you must be highly motivated and adaptable with an ability to work independently or as part of a team. Excellent organisation, communication and interpersonal skills are essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will have excellent IT skills including the ability to use a range of IT applications e.g. Microsoft Office, Outlook, Word and Excel.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameSharon LanganJob titleBusiness Support OfficerEmail addresssharon.langan@Stockport.nhs.ukTelephone number0161 835 6470&lt;/p&gt;
